      "comment": "SOLAR SPECTRUM (1) took a tumble when crowded up close to the inside last time over 525m at The Meadows. Rates strongly on best and well worth another try. LAID BACK LASS (2) has a terrific record this track and trip with five wins and four placings from nine starts. Was out of the placings last time (16.72) at Healesville in a Special conditions race, finishing fifth and beaten 4.5 lengths. Makes strong appeal on best. NAUGHTY NORM (7) was a winner two back when prominent throughout then got further back last time and could manage only a 4.5 lengths 4th at Geelong (22.84). Has ability and can atone. KALUNA CHAOS (3) is a last-start placegetter who is in the mix again.",
